<TEXT>
a national survey has found that up to 
50 percent of vietnams children are malnourished according to the 
official vietnam news agency reports 
fifteen percent of the malnutrition cases are serious or very 
serious says the recent government survey of nearly 13000 
households in 20 provinces and cities the agency reported monday 
it said the survey found that 62 percent of men and 38 percent 
of women were underweight 
the study said the average vietnamese had the worlds highest 
rate of rice consumption but the diet lacked sufficient protein 
fat vitamins and minerals 
vietnams economy is one of the worlds poorest and the 
majority of its 65 million people work the land the economy was 
hurt by rigid communism until recent reforms and by a western aid 
embargo after vietnam invaded cambodia in late 1978 
there are clear signs the reforms have produced good results 
vietnam has harvested its second good rice crop in a row and 
its target of producing some 22 million tons of food this year is 
attainable the vietnam news agency said it said farmers reaped 
nearly 12 million tons of rice in the summer and autumn harvests 
up by 400000 tons from last year 
the report also said inflation remains under control 
although it continued at 33 percent per month during this years 
first three quarters 
</TEXT>
