<TEXT>
made in germany appears on much of 
iraqs mighty arsenal from missiles to poison gas rocket fuel to 
helicopters 
six iraqi poison gas plants were built with german help 
according to an independent report commissioned by german 
authorities 
other companies allegedly delivered technology and knowhow that 
helped iraq upgrade sovietmade missiles obtain parts for a 
supercannon and acquire equipment needed to produce nuclear 
weapons 
reports by german media and foreign groups about the involvement 
of german companies aroused anger in foreign capitals including 
washington and among jewish groups at home and abroad opposition 
politicians in germany demand stronger export controls even a ban 
on arms deliveries outside nato countries 
prosecutors are investigating dozens of companies and some 
arrests have been made two company officials have confessed to 
helping iraq obtain the technology to make chemical weapons 
the government already tainted by the scandal two years ago of 
german involvement in a libyan poison gas factory says it is 
considering steps to curb illegal arms exports 
that will not be easy in a country whose economy is based on 
exports 
there is no doubt that german companies participated in the 
iraqi rocket program said norbert gansel a member of parliament 
from the oppositon social democrats and an expert on arms exports 
i am not saying that the government wanted it to be that 
way he told the associated press 
gansel said the government had taken intelligence reports on 
involvement in illegal weapons sales to iraq all too lightly 
german law forbids arms exports to areas of tension gansel said 
german companies convicted of illegal dealings with iraq should 
have their arms producing licenses revoked 
economics minister helmut haussmann has proposed milder steps 
he wants each company to name a manager of weapons exports who 
could be held responsible if export laws were broken 
other countries also delivered war material to iraq but the 
level of technology provided by german companies allowed saddam to 
pursue poison gas and missile programs according to reports in der 
spiegel a weekly news magazine 
a report commissioned by the simon wiesenthal center in los 
angeles lists 86 german companies that helped iraq become a 
military power 
raymond seitz assistant us secretary of state told congress 
this month there were german footprints all over equipment 
shipped to iraq in recent years but acknowledged it is not 
exclusively a german problem 
in a fact sheet published six days after iraq seized kuwait on 
aug 2 the stockholm international peace research institute said 
germany was far behind some other nations in providing military 
hardware to iraq in the last decade 
it said the soviet union france and china three permanent 
members of the un security council were the main suppliers in 
that period 
the moral question is especially troubling for germany 
saddam has threatened to attack israel with chemical weapons 
poison gas was developed and used by the germans during world war 
i and was used to kill jews in nazi gas chambers 
spiegel said a german company helped iraq develop a 
highperformance fuel that increased the range of its rockets 
ian anthony a coauthor of the stockholm institutes report 
sad it was hard to stop illegal exports from wetern europe 
there are virtually no border controls in the european 
economic community he said in a telephone interview it is 
very very difficult for governments with rather limited resources 
to enforce the regulations that exist 
a high official of germanys federal customs office said 98 
percent of arms exports are shipped in parts making them difficult 
to track 
many goods also fall in the dualuse category allowing 
companies to claim they did not know their equipment was destined 
for military use the official said on condition of anonymity 
he said iraq often ordered equipment from small firms that had 
financial problems but some of germanys bestknown companies also 
have been implicated 
according to spiegel messerschmittboelkowblohm helped iraq 
obtain the fuel air explosive bomb which sprays fuel into the 
air and ignites the mixture of fuel and air creating a huge 
fireball and a shock wave comparable in strength to a small nuclear 
explosion 
the company a major defense contractor denied the allegations 
it said a study was conducted for the egyptian government but the 
project was discontinued in 1988 spiegel said iraq obtained the 
study through egypt 
much of spiegels reporting has been based on a confidential 
report delivered to parliament in august by haussmann the 
economics minister 
according to the magazine haussmanns report said mediumsized 
german companies were deeply involved in supplying iraq with parts 
and the knowhow to upgrade sovietmade scudb rockets 
another company named by spiegel was water engineering trading 
gmbh of hamburg which it said supplied iraq with chemicals to 
produce nerve gas 
two managers at the company have admitted to prosecutors that 
they helped iraq obtain equipment to make poison gas both also had 
spent several years with german intelligence 
</TEXT>
