<TEXT>
the golfcrazy japanese are flocking to 
thailand to enjoy low greens fees friendly caddies and courses 
laid out by some of the worlds top designers 
thailand is in a golf boom mana sookbank honorary secretary of 
the thailand golf association said there are 60 courses in 
operation 40 under construction and many more planned 
for the japanese golfing in thailand costs a fraction of what 
it does at home they are joined by burgeoning ranks of domestic 
players from corporate climbers to prime minister chatichai 
choonhavan who conducts a lot of political business on the links 
players soon will be able to tee off near the river kwai where 
allied prisoners died by the thousands building a railway for the 
japanese in world war ii and in the hills of the infamous golden 
triangle opium region 
a complex of courses hotels and an airstrip billed as asias 
largest golf development will stretch along the gulf of siam 
southwest of bangkok it is to include a meditation center 
thailands boom comes at a fortunate time said desmond 
muirhead a leading golf course designer instead of building 
secondrate courses by themselves like the japanese did after 
world war ii the thais are getting top foreign talent 
muirhead a briton based in the united states said he plans to 
design at least five courses in thailand and has begun work on the 
century country club in the eastern coastal province of rayong 
the 100 million project includes individual homes 
condominiums a hotel and two golf courses one by muirhead and the 
other by topranked professional nick faldo among the other big 
names at work in thailand are jack nicklaus arnold palmer and greg 
norman 
people are going to beat a path from all over to play these 
courses muirhead said in an interview we expect them to be 
more visually pleasing than those in the united states 
