francisco is the product of merger accomplished in 1856 
proponents including environmental business and 
goodgovernment groups say the merger would allow the county to 
get a handle on runaway growth and development and make possible 
more efficient centralized decisionmaking 
the idea behind it is to create a more efficient provider of 
services said paul hahn deputy executive director of a local 
government commission appointed two years ago to study the issue 
right now there is a lot of duplication of effort two 
police departments two public works departments a police and 
sheriffs department they dont always coordinate with each 
other he said 
foes of the plan include independent developers and those who 
have led efforts in recent years to incorporate new cities in 
fastgrowing sacramento county 
