soviet legislature would fail threatening the future of democratic 
forces in the soviet union 
the plan calls for such steps as encouraging small private 
business and ending many state monopolies 
popov predicted the soviet leadership would adopt more radical 
free market measures if the plan does not take hold within a few 
months he said he might passively resist the conservative 
restructuring program and carry out a more radical economic program 
in his city 
