out of their embassy in kuwait where they had endured siegelike 
conditions for weeks the seven diplomats were aboard the jetliner 
when it flew into baghdad from kuwait with more than 50 freed 
hostages that group was joined by about 210 french citizens 
waiting at the baghdad airport 
the plane also carried nine greeks four britons two filipinos 
one german and one spanish citizen freed by iraq according to a 
witness at the airport 
