amtrak has initiated a faster passenger train 
between boston and new york the new england express that is 
intended to make the 230mile trip in under four hours 
the first trip sunday almost met the mark 
the express left bostons south station at 1115 am and 
arrived at penn station in manhattan at 318 pm eight minutes 
late for an average speed of 57 mph including stops 
not bad for a first try said clifford black an amtrak 
spokesman 
the trip has taken about four hours and 40 minutes in the past 
for an average speed of about 45 mph 
by comparison japans bullet trains travel at about 130 
mph and frances highspeed trains hit about 200 mph both have 
exclusive use of allnew tracks 
amtrak officials have saved some time on all lines by making 
track and bridge repairs the new england express scheduled for 12 
trips a week each way also skips some stops included in other 
rides 
to shorten the ride even more amtrak officials want to 
electrify the entire boston to new york route at present the 
route is electrified only from new york to new haven conn where 
trains must switch from diesel to electric power or vice versa 
congress has proposed spending 125 million to begin work on 
electrifying the entire line amtrak officials estimate the cost of 
completing the job will be about 400 million 
the ultimate time goal is a trip under three hours 
the new england express requires reservations but the fare 
remains the same as other scheduled service 90 round trip for 
coach and 154 for first class 
amtrak currently serves about 2 million passengers a year 
between new york and washington dc on a faster allelectric 
line on which the fastest combination of tracks has an average 
speed of 90 mph 
train officials believe there is an even bigger market for the 
bostonnew york route it is one of the biggest business travel 
corridors in the country black said 
