the supreme court on monday allowed a state to 
impose longer sentences automatically for criminals who used guns 
the court without comment let stand a montana law used to add 
10 years to the 30year prison sentence given a man who brandished 
a gun during a pizza shop robbery 
in a separate case the court refused to let police in 
massachusetts stop and search someone solely because that person 
reportedly was carrying a handgun in public 
over a dissenting vote by justice harry a blackmun the court 
let stand a ruling by massachusetts highest court that 
investigatory stops by police are unlawful if sparked by nothing 
more than the mere possession of a handgun 
the montana law was attacked as unconstitutional because thomas 
krantz never faced any gunpossession charges state courts did not 
consider his use of the gun as a separate crime but merely as a 
sentencing factor 
the montana supreme court upheld the state law last march by a 
52 vote 
krantz was convicted of holding up a missoula pizza shop and of 
driving the getaway car for a holdup at a missoula motel a week 
later 
