<TEXT>
tax initiatives in six states could result in 
reduced bond ratings at state and local level if passed by voters 
in the nov 6 election a wall street bond rating agency warned 
moodys investors service said tax initiatives in colorado 
massachusetts montana nebraska oregon and utah could if 
approved lower the confidence financial advisers have in those 
states 
they do introduce uncertainty said george leung a moodys 
analyst this year i think certainly its reflective of the mood 
the discontent amongst voters and also reflective of economic 
conditions 
moodys said in a report released last week that the initiatives 
could have serious consequences for state and local governments 
and result in reduced bond ratings 
in all of these states with the possible exception of utah 
many questions remain about how the proposals would be 
implemented moodys said in a report last week it said courts 
and state legislatures would probably have to resolve the 
ambiguities 
bond ratings are used as a guide for investors lowered bond 
ratings can result in higher interest payments for borrowing 
most states back their bonds with the full faith and credit of 
the state making payment of debt the highest spending priority 
financially ailing massachusetts already has the lowest bond 
rating in the country bond rating agencies have warned that 
passage of a proposal to roll back certain taxes and fees there to 
1988 levels could drop the states rating from its current level of 
baa to junk bond status 
in colorado and oregon the tax initiatives set more restrictive 
limits on property taxes other revenue sources and municipal debt 
in montana the initiative would replace all sales income and 
property taxes with a trade charge on business and financial 
transactions 
one nebraska initiative would impose a cap on annual expenditure 
growth while another would change the manner in which schools are 
funded the utah initiative would remove some items from the sales 
tax base 
moodys warned that municipal bond ratings also could also 
suffer if the initiatives pass 
if montanas initiative succeeds all ratings in the state 
would immediately be placed under review because the measure calls 
for a massive restructuring of state and local revenues for both 
operations and debt service moodys said 
montana and oregon currently have ratings of aa and utah has a 
rating of aaa on general obligation bonds which are backed by the 
states full faith and credit moodys does not have a general 
obligation bond rating for either colorado and nebraska because 
the states do not issues such bonds leung said 
the massachusetts initiative would reduce the personal income 
tax rate eliminating a surcharge collected in fiscal 1990 and 
1991 and would roll back other state taxes to their august 1989 
levels 
if it passes the initiative will cost the state an estimated 
128 billion in 1991 and 255 billion the following year 
opponents of the citizens for limited taxation proposal in 
massachusetts have argued the measure would gut state government 
programs 
howard foley president of the massachusetts high tech council 
a 200company business association that cosponsored the clt 
petition said the warning should have come two years ago when the 
states bond rating was still high 
i think the biggest problem is the continuing overspending of 
what we dont have foley said when asked about the prospect of a 
bond rating reduction perhaps if that option wasnt available 
wed pay more attention to balancing our books 
