<TEXT>
a top educator on monday said the country 
needs a national education index to serve as a benchmark for 
tates to measure student achievement and pinpoint failing schools 
or ineffective local leaders 
ernest boyer president of the carnegie foundation for the 
advancement of teaching insisted during a fortune magazine 
seminar of businessmen educators and governors that the nation is 
more than ready for a national policy in education 
the message it seems to me is absolutely clear after 
years of vigorously defending local school control the nation is 
now supporting indeed almost demanding national leadership in 
education while still maintaining vitality at the local level 
its time to go beyond goals important as they are and 
begin to talk more precisely about education standards and how 
progress toward national objectives can be measured 
state must have clearly defined goals an assessment procedure 
requiring annual progress reports from schools and clearly defined 
methods of intervention in case a school is failing he said 
as part of intervention boyer said a state might put a school 
on probation or assign a senior adviser to the school who would 
spend time working with teachers counselors and administrators 
the state also should be given the authority to remove a principal 
superintendent or even a local school board 
a state might even close a school a strategy of last 
resort he said 
local school control is crucial but its insufficient in the 
end students must be served and if a school for whatever reason 
does not provide an effective education state officials have both 
a legal and moral obligation to intervene said boyer 
the index also should include 
school completion rates of students in every state this 
category would include a look at each students proficiency in 
english and mathematics performance on general knowledge tests and 
whether a state gives priority to writing 
the condition of teaching states would be judged on whether 
they have a plan for attracting outstanding students into teaching 
special strategies to attract teachers in math and science and 
requirements for training that include sabbaticals fellowships and 
teacher institutes teacher salaries also would be considered 
the schools climate as it relates to the quality of buildings 
classrooms and laboratories as well as class size 
financial support of schools states perstudent expenditures 
and other costs would be compared regionally so that costofliving 
can be considered equity in school finance would be a key 
consideration 
how schools are governed states must have clearly defined 
goals as well as intervention methods in case of a failing school 
boyer sidestepped the issue of who should be in charge of the 
national evaluation of school performance noting that both 
congress and the national governors association have been haggling 
over the issue the nga has set up a special board to handle the 
task and congress has passed two bills creating panels 
