years ireland would be the only country with a guaranteed number 
of visas 16000 per year for a total of 48000 
after 1994 up to 7700 irish would receive visas annually under 
a diversity provision of the bill designed to offset the 
unfairness of past immigration formulas in addition irish could 
apply under the traditional categories of family ties and 
employment for the latter half of the decade ireland could reach 
the maximum allowable total for any country in a year 20000 
those numbers compare to the roughly 3000 to 5000 irish visas 
issued per year in the early 1980s and about 7500 in the latter 
part of the decade 
