rupert murdoch told a shareholders 
meeting oct 23 he expects news corp ltd to increase earnings 
despite uncertainties in some of its major markets 
he did not estimate earnings and would not comment on the 
companys shortterm debt problems which have depressed news 
corps stock price in recent weeks 
shortterm debt soared last fiscal year to 230 billion from 
396 million total debt rose to 821 billion from 613 billion 
in an interview the day before the shareholders meeting murdoch 
said news corp would concentrate on film and electronic media 
rather than the newspapers and magazines he used to build the 
company 
newspapers and magazines now account for about 70 percent of 
news corp profits 
