britain and a pilot strike at the halfowned ansett australia 
airline 
stockholders approved a resolution allowing directors to issue 
limitedvoting shares murdoch wants to be able to issue such 
shares so the company can raise funds without diluting his 45 
percent stake in the company 
on oct 3 murdoch merged four of his australian newspapers into 
two aroundtheclock productions a move that reflected 
increasingly tough times in the australian media business 
</TEXT>
