from the local community 
he urged councilors to send a strong message to the 
newspaper that we wont support you economically until you serve 
this community better than you have been doing 
councilor gene bergman offered the resolution and said he hoped 
it would be discussed at the next meeting scheduled for the night 
of oct 29 
talks between the paper and workers represented by the graphic 
communication international union have been stalled since last dec 
7 when they broke down after 14 negotiating sessions workers had 
voted to unionize the previous april 
the two sides differ on estimates of how much advertising the 
city buys from the newspaper clavelle put the annual amount at 
67000 while donovan said it is closer to 30000 
