<TEXT>
the public has a right to attend 
some pretrial criminal hearings despite opposition from defendants 
the idaho supreme court ruled 
the justices in a 41 decision oct 23 imposed stiff 
requirements on defendants who want closed hearings they said the 
public would benefit from preliminary hearings conducted in open 
court 
when a preliminary hearing is closed the public is denied the 
opportunity to observe the criminal justice system at work and is 
denied the assurance that justice has been fairly and properly 
administered the opinion said 
the courts decision reverses 1st district court magistrate 
peter hutchinsons decision to close a hearing for joshua frazier 
who was accused of murder hutchinson also ordered records of the 
hearing sealed 
cowles publishing co which publishes the spokesmanreview and 
chronicle newspapers in spokane wash appealed hutchinsons 
ruling it had a reporter ejected from fraziers hearing 
