<TEXT>
age rarely stands in the way of success at 
the ballot box in michigan despite gov james blanchards highly 
publicized decision to dump his 78yearold running mate 
statewide elected officials include not only martha griffiths 
who was 70 when she was elected to her first term as lieutenant 
governor but democrats secretary of state richard austin 77 and 
attorney general frank kelley 65 both are running for new 
fouryear terms 
no one has suggested to me that i should not run again for 
any reason said austin seeking his sixth term my personal 
view is that voters generally do not regard my age in any way 
theyre concerned about how well i perform in the office 
austins republican opponent state rep judith miller 54 of 
birmingham said she has no plans to question his fitness for 
office at 77 
from my perspective whether you are young or old should not 
be the determining factor in how you function its the kind of 
thing i dont believe is a legitimate issue 
the fact that the issue of fitness was raised with griffiths 
but not with austin irked her the longtime champion of womens 
rights complained the governor never would have booted her if shed 
been a 78yearold man 
blanchard removed griffiths from the democratic ticket aug 24 
after two terms saying he no longer considers her ready to step in 
and assume the governors duties at a moments notice 
age was not a factor he said but he declined to elaborate on 
his reasons griffiths who feuded publicly with blanchard for 
weeks about the breakup of their political partnership said he 
told her she could be on the ticket if she released her medical 
records and tax returns she refused but told reporters her health 
is good 
griffiths only obvious problem is her hearing at a news 
conference responding to blanchards removal of her from the 
ticket she lost her hearing aid she and her husband searched for 
it on the floor behind the podium retrieved it and put it back in 
her ear but she still had difficulty hearing questions 
the former congresswoman keeps a busy schedule speaking to 
womens groups and presiding over the michigan senate but senators 
complained she was cranky and lectured them like schoolchildren 
under michigans constitution the lieutenant governor acts as 
governor whenever the chief executive is out of state that has 
happened 18 days so far this year 
the secretary of state is next in line austin was acting 
governor for a week in 1988 when blanchard and griffiths were at 
the democratic national convention 
austin oversees 185 offices around michigan whose 2000 
employees issue drivers licenses sell license plates and register 
voters his schedule runs 12 to 15 hours a day with no annual 
vacations said his scheduler ann johnson 
he looks lean and fit and credits that to habits developed as an 
athlete which included time as high school track team captain 
hurdles were my favorite event he said somehow i can 
still visualize myself skimming over those hurdles i wouldnt try 
it today 
austin walks six to eight miles every sunday to keep his legs in 
shape thats half the battle he said 
age is less of a hurdle for incumbents like austin than 
challengers said david rohde professor of political science at 
michigan state university 
its much easier for the electorate to be convinced the person 
is qualified to serve regardless of age if the person already is 
serving he said 
but the fitness of an elderly person for office is an individual 
matter just as it is for younger candidates he said partly it 
depends on how visibly capable and vigorous the candidate is 
in floridas democratic primary for governor bill nelson 48 
tried to make age an issue calling for a new generation of 
leadership his opponent lawton chiles 61 won the primary and 
age has not been an issue in the general election 
