chrysler corp today reported it 
lost 214 million in the third quarter nearly offsetting the 251 
million it earned in the first six months of 1990 
the loss which amounts to 95 cents a share was a little less 
than expected by wall street analysts and stemmed mainly from 
incentive costs and lower production caused when minivan plants 
were retooled 
the earnings report came as chrysler faced a midnight expiration 
of a contract it negotiated with the united auto workers union in 
1988 
during the third quarter of last year chrysler earned 331 
million or 142 a share the 1989 results were boosted by a 
onetime credit of 309 million from the sale of a stake in 
mitsubishi motors corp of japan 
chrysler said the thirdquarter 1990 loss came on revenues of 
65 billion down 145 percent from 76 billion during the 
julyseptember period last year 
the companys thirdquarter losses were softened by 83 million 
in earnings for chrysler financial corp that profit a record for 
any third quarter in chryslers history compares with 
thirdquarter earnings last year of 76 million 
for the first nine months of the year chrysler earned 37 
million or 17 cents a share compared with 983 million or 421 
a share during the same time last year revenue fell 154 percent 
to 23 billion from 272 billion 
we anticipated 1990 would be a tough year for chrysler and for 
the industry so we launched a major costcutting program over a 
year ago company chairman lee iacocca said today we didnt 
anticipate the gulf crisis the federal budget fiasco or the 
continued escalation in the incentive wars so weve increased our 
costreduction goals to 25 billion over two years 
iacocca has set the target for june 1991 
chrysler took its minivan plants in st louis and in windsor 
ontario out of service for a month to retool for 1991 models 
damaging profits by reducing wholesale sales to dealers minivans 
and to a lesser extent jeeps are the bases for chryslers 
profits 
the company also is being hit by high incentive costs the big 
three would like to end the cash rebates and lowinterest 
financing but each is waiting for another to take the first step 
ford motor co reports its earnings tuesday the same day 
general motors corp releases its thirdquarter profit figures for 
its major subsidiaries and the day before it reports corporate 
earnings 
analysts have speculated fords earnings will be about 47 
percent below the 255 million it earned during the quarter last 
year and gms will be half of the 248 million it made during the 
period last year 
collectively thirdquarter earnings for the big three were 
expected to be about 80 percent lower than last year 
fords and gms overseas earnings continue to sag analysts have 
said hurting their corporate profits nearly all of chryslers 
operations are in the united states 
