1089 
louisiana added nine rigs for the week while oklahoma wyoming 
california north dakota pennsylvania and texas also added rigs 
counts in other major producing states remained unchanged 
baker hughes has kept track of the rig count since 1940 it is a 
widely watched index of drilling activity and represents the number 
of rigs actively exploring for oil not those producing oil 
at the height of the oil boom in december 1981 the count 
reached a peak of 4500 but the rig count plunged to a low of 663 
after oil prices collapsed in the summer of 1986 
